div.p: You are a film-critic analyst.
Read the review and decide what kind of movies the reviewer tends to enjoy.
Classify the review into ONE of these six "Reviewer Taste Segments":
1. "Realism Seekers" prefer believable stories and authentic emotion.
2. "Plot Critics" judge films by story logic and writing quality.
3. "Melodrama Buffs" drawn to emotional or romantic stories.
4. "Entertainment Seekers" enjoy fun, fast-paced, or action-heavy films.
5. "Genre Loyalists" consistently favor or dislike specific genres.
6. "Other / Unclassifiable" no clear or consistent taste signal.
Return JSON in this exact format:
"taste_label": "<one of the six segments above>",
"keywords": ["<1-3 words that influenced your choice>"],
"rationale": "<choose one basis only: tone | emotion | implicit meaning | structure | overall impression | keywords>"
Guidance:
Choose the option that best reflects what influenced your decision most.
Use 'keywords' only when classification depends mainly on explicit words such as genre names or direct sentiment terms.
